  <!-- ========== SECTION 1: CODING STANDARDS ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section" id="coding-standards" aria-label="Coding Standards and Style">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[01]</span>
        <h2>Coding Standards &amp; Style</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Consistent code is maintainable code. Establish style rules early and enforce them automatically.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <!-- Practice Card 1.1 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"></path><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"></polyline><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"></line><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"></line><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">All Languages</span>
              <span class="tag">Essential</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Use a Consistent Code Style</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Pick a style guide (Airbnb, Google, StandardJS) and follow it across your entire codebase. Consistency reduces cognitive load and makes onboarding faster.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>function getData( ){
  var x=  getUser()
    if(x){return x.name }
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>function getData() {
  const user = getUser();
  if (user) {
    return user.name;
  }
  return null;
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Choose one style guide per language
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Configure ESLint / Prettier / EditorConfig
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Enforce in CI pipeline — fail builds on lint errors
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Practice Card 1.2 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5"></polyline><line x1="12" y1="19" x2="20" y2="19"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Naming</span>
              <span class="tag">Readability</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Meaningful Naming Conventions</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Names should reveal intent. A variable, function, or class name should tell you why it exists, what it does, and how it's used — without needing a comment.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>const d = new Date();
const arr = users.filter(u => u.a > 18);
function proc(x) { /* ... */ }</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>const createdAt = new Date();
const adultUsers = users.filter(
  user => user.age > 18
);
function processPayment(order) { /* ... */ }</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Use descriptive, pronounceable names
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Booleans: prefix with is, has, can, should
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Functions: use verb + noun (getUserById, calculateTotal)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Practice Card 1.3 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"></line><line x1="9" y1="21" x2="9" y2="9"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Architecture</span>
              <span class="tag">SOLID</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Single Responsibility Principle</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Every function, class, and module should do one thing and do it well. If you can't describe what it does in one sentence, it's doing too much.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>function handleUser(user) {
  validate(user);
  saveToDatabase(user);
  sendWelcomeEmail(user);
  logAnalytics('signup', user);
  updateLeaderboard(user);
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>function registerUser(user) {
  const validated = validateUser(user);
  const saved = userRepository.save(validated);
  eventBus.emit('user:registered', saved);
}
// Listeners handle email, analytics, etc.</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              One reason to change per module
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Extract side effects into separate handlers
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Functions under 20 lines, files under 300 lines
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Practice Card 1.4 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 20h9"></path><path d="M16.5 3.5a2.121 2.121 0 0 1 3 3L7 19l-4 1 1-4L16.5 3.5z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Clean Code</span>
              <span class="tag">DRY</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Don't Repeat Yourself (DRY)</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Every piece of knowledge should have a single, unambiguous, authoritative representation. Duplicate code means duplicate bugs and double maintenance effort.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>// In checkout.js
const tax = price * 0.18;
const total = price + tax;

// In invoice.js
const invoiceTax = amount * 0.18;
const invoiceTotal = amount + invoiceTax;</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>// tax.js
const TAX_RATE = 0.18;
function calculateTotal(price) {
  const tax = price * TAX_RATE;
  return { tax, total: price + tax };
}
// Used everywhere via import</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Extract shared logic into utility functions
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Use constants for magic numbers and strings
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              But avoid premature abstraction — rule of three
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Practice Card 1.5 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"></line><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Error Handling</span>
              <span class="tag">Reliability</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Handle Errors Gracefully</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Never swallow errors silently. Catch specific exceptions, provide meaningful messages, and fail gracefully. Unhandled errors in production destroy user trust.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>try {
  await saveUser(data);
} catch (e) {
  // TODO: handle later
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>try {
  await saveUser(data);
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof ValidationError) {
    return res.status(400).json({
      message: error.message,
    });
  }
  logger.error('User save failed', { error });
  return res.status(500).json({
    message: 'Something went wrong.',
  });
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Catch specific error types, not generic catch-all
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Log errors with context for debugging
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Return user-friendly messages, never stack traces
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <!-- Practice Card 1.6 -->
        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Comments</span>
              <span class="tag">Readability</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Comment Why, Not What</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Good code is self-documenting. Use comments to explain <em>why</em> something is done, not <em>what</em> the code does. If you need to explain what, the code needs refactoring.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>// Loop through users
for (const u of users) {
  // Check if age is greater than 18
  if (u.age > 18) {
    // Add to results array
    results.push(u);
  }
}</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>// Legal requirement: GDPR mandates age
// verification before data processing
const eligibleUsers = users.filter(
  user => user.age > 18
);</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Explain business rules and edge cases
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Delete commented-out code — Git remembers
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Use JSDoc/TSDoc for public API documentation
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
