  <!-- ========== SECTION 4: VERSION CONTROL ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section bp-section--alt" id="version-control" aria-label="Version Control and Git">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[04]</span>
        <h2>Version Control &amp; Git</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Git is your safety net and collaboration backbone. Use it with discipline and intention.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="18" cy="18" r="3"></circle><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="3"></circle><path d="M13 6h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v7"></path><line x1="6" y1="9" x2="6" y2="21"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Git</span>
              <span class="tag">Commits</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Write Atomic Commits</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Each commit should represent one logical change. Small, focused commits are easier to review, revert, bisect, and cherry-pick.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-bad">✗ Avoid</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>git commit -m "fixed stuff and added feature
and updated deps"</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Prefer</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>git commit -m "fix: resolve null pointer in
user validation (#142)"

git commit -m "feat: add email notification
on order placement"

git commit -m "chore: update express to 4.19"</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Use Conventional Commits: feat, fix, chore, docs
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Reference issue numbers in commit messages
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              One concern per commit — never mix refactor + feature
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="6" y1="3" x2="6" y2="15"></line><circle cx="18" cy="6" r="3"></circle><circle cx="6" cy="18" r="3"></circle><path d="M18 9a9 9 0 0 1-9 9"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Branching</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Use a Branching Strategy</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Adopt Git Flow, GitHub Flow, or Trunk-Based Development. Consistency in branching prevents merge chaos and deployment accidents.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ GitHub Flow</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>main (always deployable)
  └── feature/add-user-auth
  └── fix/login-redirect-bug
  └── chore/update-dependencies

Workflow:
1. Branch from main
2. Make changes + commit
3. Open Pull Request
4. Code review + CI passes
5. Merge to main → auto-deploy</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Never push directly to main / production
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Short-lived branches — merge within 1-2 days
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Delete branches after merge
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"></path><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"></line><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Security</span>
              <span class="tag">.gitignore</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Never Commit Secrets</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">API keys, passwords, tokens, and .env files must never enter your repository. Once committed, they're in the history forever — even if you delete the file.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ .gitignore</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code># Environment
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Secrets
*.pem
*.key
credentials.json</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Set up .gitignore before first commit
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Use git-secrets or pre-commit hooks to scan
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>
              Rotate any key that was ever committed
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 5: CODE REVIEW ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section" id="code-review" aria-label="Code Review">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[05]</span>
        <h2>Code Review</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Code review is a team multiplier. It catches bugs, spreads knowledge, and raises the quality bar for everyone.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Process</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Review Every Pull Request</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">No code reaches main without at least one peer review. Reviews catch bugs, enforce standards, and distribute knowledge across the team.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Require at least 1 approval before merge</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Review within 24 hours — don't block teammates</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Check logic, security, tests, naming, edge cases</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Be constructive — critique the code, not the person</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"></path><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"></polyline><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"></line><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">PR Quality</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Write Good PR Descriptions</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">A good PR tells the reviewer what changed, why, and how to test it. Include screenshots for UI changes. Link the issue. Describe the approach.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ PR Template</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>## What
Added email verification on signup.

## Why
Reduces spam accounts by 80% (Issue #234).

## How to test
1. Register with a new email
2. Check inbox for verification link
3. Click link → account activated

## Screenshots
[before] → [after]</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Keep PRs under 400 lines — split large features</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use a PR template for consistency</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Self-review before requesting others</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 6: SECURITY ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section bp-section--alt" id="security" aria-label="Security Best Practices">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[06]</span>
        <h2>Security Best Practices</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Security is not a feature — it's a requirement. Think about security at every layer from day one.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Input</span>
              <span class="tag">Critical</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Validate &amp; Sanitize All Input</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Never trust user input. Validate type, length, format, and range on the server. Sanitize to prevent XSS and SQL injection. Client-side validation is UX, not security.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ Express Validator</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code>const { body, validationResult } = require(
  'express-validator'
);

app.post('/api/contact', [
  body('email').isEmail().normalizeEmail(),
  body('name').trim().isLength({ min: 1,
    max: 100 }).escape(),
  body('message').trim().isLength({ min: 10,
    max: 2000 }).escape(),
], (req, res) => {
  const errors = validationResult(req);
  if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
    return res.status(400).json({
      errors: errors.array()
    });
  }
  // Safe to process
});</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Validate on server — never rely on client alone</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use parameterized queries — never concatenate SQL</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Escape HTML output to prevent XSS</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Auth</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Secure Authentication</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Hash passwords with bcrypt (cost factor ≥ 10). Use HTTPS everywhere. Implement rate limiting on login endpoints. Never store plaintext passwords.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>bcrypt with salt rounds ≥ 10</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Rate limit login to 5 attempts per minute</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Set secure, httpOnly, sameSite on session cookies</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use helmet() for security headers</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 2l-2 2m-7.61 7.61a5.5 5.5 0 1 1-7.778 7.778 5.5 5.5 0 0 1 7.777-7.777zm0 0L15.5 7.5m0 0l3 3L22 7l-3-3m-3.5 3.5L19 4"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Dependencies</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Keep Dependencies Updated</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Outdated packages are the #1 attack vector. Run npm audit regularly. Use Dependabot or Renovate for automated updates. Pin versions in production.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Run npm audit weekly</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Enable Dependabot on GitHub</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use package-lock.json — commit it</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Review changelogs before major updates</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 7: PERFORMANCE ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section" id="performance" aria-label="Performance Optimization">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[07]</span>
        <h2>Performance Optimization</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Fast software is good software. Measure first, optimize second, and never guess where the bottleneck is.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Frontend</span>
              <span class="tag">Core Web Vitals</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Optimize Core Web Vitals</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">LCP, FID, and CLS directly affect search rankings and user experience. Defer non-critical JS, lazy load images, use explicit dimensions, and minimize layout shifts.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use defer on all script tags</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Set width and height on every image</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use loading="lazy" below the fold</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Enable gzip/brotli compression</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Backend</span>
              <span class="tag">Database</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Optimize Database Queries</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Slow queries are the silent killer of application performance. Index frequently queried columns, avoid N+1 queries, use connection pooling, and monitor query times.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Add indexes on columns used in WHERE and JOIN</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use EXPLAIN to analyze slow queries</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use connection pooling (mysql2 pool)</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>SELECT only columns you need — never SELECT *</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"></polyline><polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"></polyline><path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0 1 14.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 0 20.49 15"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">Caching</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Cache Strategically</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Cache static assets with long max-age headers. Cache API responses where appropriate. Use ETags. But always have a cache invalidation strategy.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Static assets: Cache-Control max-age 7+ days</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use content hashing in filenames for cache busting</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>API: cache GET responses, invalidate on mutations</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== SECTION 8: DOCUMENTATION ========== -->
  <section class="bp-section bp-section--alt" id="documentation" aria-label="Documentation and Communication">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bp-section-header">
        <span class="section-number">[08]</span>
        <h2>Documentation &amp; Communication</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="bp-section-desc">Great documentation is the difference between a project that scales and one that dies when the original author leaves.</p>

      <div class="bp-grid">

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"></path><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">README</span>
              <span class="tag">Essential</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Write a Comprehensive README</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Your README is your project's front door. Include what it does, how to install it, how to run it, how to contribute, and license information. A bad README kills adoption.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ README Structure</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code># Project Name
One-line description.

## Features
- Feature 1
- Feature 2

## Quick Start
$ git clone ...
$ npm install
$ npm run dev

## Environment Variables
Copy .env.example to .env

## Contributing
See CONTRIBUTING.md

## License
MIT</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Include badges (build status, coverage, license)</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Keep it updated — stale docs are worse than none</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Add screenshots/GIFs for visual projects</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M11 4H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7"></path><path d="M18.5 2.5a2.121 2.121 0 0 1 3 3L12 15l-4 1 1-4 9.5-9.5z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">API Docs</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Document Your APIs</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Every endpoint needs documentation: URL, method, parameters, request body, response format, status codes, and examples. Use OpenAPI/Swagger for auto-generated docs.</p>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Document every endpoint with request/response examples</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Include error responses and status codes</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Use OpenAPI spec for auto-generated docs</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Version your API from day one</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="bp-card">
          <div class="bp-card-top">
            <span class="bp-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="bp-card-tags">
              <span class="tag">ADR</span>
              <span class="tag">Team</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="bp-card-title">Record Architecture Decisions</h3>
          <p class="bp-card-desc">Use Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) to document why you chose a technology, pattern, or approach. Future you (and your team) will thank you.</p>
          <div class="bp-card-example">
            <div class="bp-card-example-header">
              <span class="bp-example-label bp-example-good">✓ ADR Format</span>
            </div>
            <pre><code># ADR-001: Use MySQL over PostgreSQL

## Status: Accepted
## Date: 2026-02-27

## Context
Hosting provider includes MySQL free.

## Decision
Use MySQL with mysql2 driver.

## Consequences
+ Zero additional cost
+ Native phpMyAdmin support
- Fewer JSON features than Postgres</code></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="bp-card-checklist">
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Store ADRs in docs/adr/ in your repo</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Record context, decision, and consequences</li>
            <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg>Never delete ADRs — supersede them</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

